text: Grønnåsen Church is a church located in the northern part of Tromsø city on Tromsøya island in Norway. It was built in 1996 and has a fan-shaped design. The church can hold about 450 people and is used by the Grønnåsen parish. == References == Category:Buildings and structures in Troms Category:Churches in Tromsø
title: Grønnåsen Church
